@startuml
title TPL Conceptual Domain - Tasking

hide methods
hide stereotypes
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
left to right direction

class User
class Patient
class Episode
class ColloqiumAgenda
class Coordination

class TaskGroupTemplate
class TaskTemplate
class TaskGroup
class Task

TaskGroupTemplate "1" -- "0..*" TaskTemplate
TaskGroupTemplate "1" -- "0..*" TaskGroup
TaskGroup "1" -- "0..*" Task

Patient "1" <-- "0..*" TaskGroup : context (optional)
Episode "1" <-- "0..*" TaskGroup : context (optional)
ColloqiumAgenda "1" <-- "0..*" TaskGroup : context (optional)
Coordination "1" <-- "0..*" TaskGroup : context (optional)

User "1" <-- "0..*" Task : assigned to (optional)
User "1" <-- "0..*" Task : closed by (optional)

note bottom of TaskGroup
Exactly one domain context is typically active:
Patient OR Episode OR ColloqiumAgenda OR Coordination.
This is a conceptual intent, even if represented
with multiple nullable references in persistence.
end note

